EmailTemplate.name: STH Eric Smith hiring Heros
EmailTemplate.subject: Great News!
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear {!Contact.FirstName},
Yesterday was a huge day for our Combat to Careers campaign. Building on your work during Storm the Hill, SVAC Chairwoman Patty Murray introduced The Hiring Heroes Act of 2011. She held a press conference with Senators Begich (AK), Tester (MT), and Coons (DE) and one of your own: Eric Smith. Eric spoke at yesterday's press conference, doing what you all did so well at Storm the Hill: tell your stories. Eric rocked and represented you well.
Remember training day and your asks during the meeting? The bill includes key provisions that you advocated for during Storm the Hill, including commissioning a study to translate military skills to their civilian equivalents and mandating TAP for all servicemembers. You can read more about the press conference and the bill at <http://iava.org/blog/iava-member-veterans-help-announce-critical-jobs-legislation>.
Yesterday was a huge victory for us but we still have a lot of work to do to make this bill a law. We’ll continue to call on you to lead until we get this bill the President's desk.
Be proud,
Jonathan
-- Jonathan Schleifer
Policy Director
